Results.ReviewText: I bought this a month ago when someone in Tesco recommended it to me. I love the taste of coffee but I cannot handle caffeine! It makes my anxiety a bit worse. This decaf version of Nescafe Gold was made for me. It gives me the incredible taste I crave and a small buzz that gets me through the day at work. I also have it with almond milk as I don't have dairy and it makes for a beautiful combination!
Results.Title: Tasty pick me up without the intensity of caffeine

Results.ReviewText: I bought this decaff coffee a month ago, because I couldn't get my usual one. Well I must admit that I am glad I couldn't get my usual. This one is much nicer. My husband and I cannot drink caffeinated coffee as he suffers with the after effects of a massive stroke and I get cluster migraines if I drink too much caffeinated coffee. We definitely won't be going back to our usual decaffeinated coffee
Results.Title: Delicious

Results.ReviewText: Some decaff coffee has a very odd taste - just not right, whereas Nescafe Gold blend Decaff doesn't have that odd taste that others do. I first started drinking it at a friends. I'd been drinking it for months and months when she told me that I'd been drinking decaff - I honestly had no idea. I now buy it myself and really enjoy the taste. It tastes like proper coffee - which is all I'm asking for!
Results.Title: Doesn't taste like Decaff (which is a good thing!)

Results.ReviewText: Over a year ago I decided I needed to start eating more healthy. I really enjoy drinking coffee and I have been looking for a Decaff coffee for some time! I decided to give NESCAFÉ GOLD BLEND Decaff  ago and couldn't believe I was drinking Decaff, I had to check the label several times, the taste is incredible and I couldn't taste the difference between NESCAFÉ GOLD BLEND Decaff  and real Coffee
Results.Title: Can you taste the difference?

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, NESCAFÉ Alta Rica, Cap Colombie & Espresso now come in the new champagne gold jars as they are now part of the NESCAFÉ Gold range. Each of them still have a coloured label on the front to ensure consumers can still find them in store.

Results.ReviewText:
Have I bought nescafe gold? Nescafe black? Nescafe alta rica? 
All the packaging is similar. Does it suggest all coffee is similar? 
There seems to be nothing on the packaging to set them apart. The packaging is similar to the collections range. Does this mean they are being incorporated and given new names?
How long do I have to stand and read the labels before I get a coffee taste I enjoy?
Results.Title: Difficult packaging.

Results.ReviewText:
The distinct blue touches to this well known symbolic jar are the only indicators that I am drinking a decaffeinated cup of coffee. This product truly belongs to the gold range and deserves a gold medal - without realising it, I was using all 5 senses whilst revelling in this drinking experience! 

My ears took in the crispness of sound as the granules fell into my mug
My eyes beheld the golden hues of colour 
My sense of touch heightened as I wrapped my fingers around my coffee cup
My nose inhaled the rich and aromatic vapours emanating from my mug
My taste buds were overloaded by the full-bodied flavour of the liquid nectar

This truly is multiple snippets of heaven in a glass jar - available at your supermarket or other on-line retaillers. An extra bonus - its organic and the decaffeination process has no chemicals!!

Seriously - you have to try it - this is an absolute winner !!!!!
Results.Title: A drinking experience to overload all 5 senses!!

Results.ReviewText: I've recently been cutting down on my caffeine intake, and I had the opportunity to try this. I was really surprised with the taste. I wouldn't have noticed this was decaffeinated (I know caffeine isn't a taste, but I guess it's a psychological thing), so I don't feel as if I'm missing out.  I tried it black and with milk and was impressed with both. I'll definitely be buying this again.
Results.Title: I was very pleasantly surprised!

Results.ReviewText: Trying to control my caffeine intake but wary of decaff options.  Picked up this and the price was competitive, wasn't expecting much.  I have bought the normal Gold in the past and wouldn't have known it wasn't the normal version if I hadn't bought it specifically. A full coffee flavour without tasting like they've included the floor sweepings (like some own brands I won't mention).
Results.Title: Pleasant, well priced decaf instant

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks very much for letting us know your thoughts on the new recipe. We really appreciate your feedback! The residue you can see at the bottom of your cup is micro ground coffee that was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend during the recent change. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee!

Results.ReviewText: I have been buying Gold Blend Decaf for many, many years and have always loved it. This new concoction is dreadful. It simply doesn’t dissolve! It leaves scum in the cup  that makes the last inch or so undrinkable. It doesn’t even taste good. If it isn’t broke don’t fix it was never more applicable. I will never buy this again until it changes radically. What on Earth have you done?
Results.Title: Absolutely awful

Results.ReviewText: When I saw this coffee in the supermarket I just knew I had to buy it.  I am over the moon that I have.  Many other decaff coffees just donot have the body, flavour and aroma that this coffee has.  Alll guests have been served this coffee and tell me that they intend to purchase it in the future - no better recommendation as my friends are extremly picky with their choices!!
Results.Title: Unbeatable

Results.ReviewText: I love this decaff, ever since I weaned myself off my caffeine addiction  have been vaguely dissatisfied with my coffee and reduced my intake to almost nothing. However after trying this blend I will definitely be drinking more. I especially love my milky coffee before bed, all of the taste and creaminess  and it smells divine and I know it will not disturb my sleep.
Results.Title: Great taste

Results.ReviewText: Having my favourite Necafe Gold Blend coffee late at night doesn't keep me awake, in fact when I have Nescafe Gold Blend Decaf I have the best night's sleep ever and I wake up so refreshed in the morning that I feel great! For my daytime treat I revert back to my usual caffinated Necafe Gold Blend which I love ice cold or steaming hot. Top marks to Necafe.
Results.Title: My dreamy night time treat

Results.ReviewText: My friend had the coffee i loved it . I found it very hard to find a descent  decaf coffee and a descent price as most coffee is pricy especially decaf for some strange reason . I will recomend this to all my family and friends as it is the best out on the market yet.  Well done to u for making my day perfect now with decaf i can say i enjoy . Thank u .
Results.Title: Great easy jar to open and very good clear labelin

Results.ReviewText: I have used this coffee for as long as I can remember.  I|t has been re packaged and the taste has changed and not for the better either.  It now has a slightly more bitter taste and seems somehow thinner taste too.  Why change something that clearly we all liked anyway. Also dont like the sediment it now leaves in the cup. Disappointing
Results.Title: not as good as original

Results.ReviewText:
I Love this coffee,
I cannot drink caffeinated coffee, as it makes me feel agitated and anxious as I am sensitive to caffeine in this way. The taste of Gold Blend is perfect. I always have decaff in my coffee caddy and when visitors comment that I always serve a lovely cup of coffee it makes me smile that they do't know its decaff !
Results.Title: Nescafe Gold Blend Decaff

Results.ReviewText:
Hi, 
I struggle with caffeine as it gives me horrendous headaches so I searched far and wide to find a decent decaf coffee that I like, I have tried many alternatives  and I always come back to nescafè gold, it is by far the best in my opinion,  with the same flavour as full coffee, I would recommend this as it is great value too.
Results.Title: Great tasting decaf

Results.ReviewText: I bought this coffee for a few friends and family I have who like decaff. However, I tried some myself and was very pleasantly surprised. In terms of taste and sort of coffeeness I cannot tell the difference. Admittedly, I am not a connoisseur and I like my coffee medium and  milky i.e. a latte but I really enjoyed this decaff.
Results.Title: Tastes Great

Results.ReviewText: As a coffee afficianado I do tend to switch too Decaf in the evening and Gold blend decaff ticks all the boxes, manages to capture the full smooth rich flavour of Gold Blend with a slightly floral note. Apart from my early morning start the day cuppa have now almost entirely switched too decaf as i cannot tell the difference.
Results.Title: Agreat tasting Decaf

Results.ReviewText:
On the advice of my doctor I have decided to switch to Decaf. I love my coffee and have been searching high and low for the perfect decaf coffee.....and now I have found it.
Nescafe Gold Blend Decaf is rich but smooth with a wonderful aroma and taste. 
Great value for money and still allows me to get my perfect coffee fix.
Results.Title: Delicious

Results.ReviewText: I was a bit dubious and sceptical about trying a decaff coffee. I expected the taste to be totally different from Gold Blend which I have used and loved for years. Pleased to say that I was wrong to be worried. I can have the best of both worlds, same exquisite tate and quality but in a decaff form. A very happy convert.
Results.Title: I am a convert

Results.ReviewText:
I drink Nescafe Decaf on a daily basis. In fact it's my main drink! It is by far the best Decaf on the market. Many decaffineated coffees fall short of flavour but this product equals it's caffineated partner. 
On a down side not keen on the new packaging which make the Gold Range from Nescafe difficult to distinguish.
Results.Title: Best Decaf available

Results.ReviewText: I use Nescafe Gold Blend Decaff because it still has all the rich taste and aroma of caffeinated coffee, I love to sit back and relax about 11am with my large cup of Gold Blend in my hand making the house smell of the gorgeous aroma, I can sit ,sip and dream, Gold Blend Decaff always makes me smile. Thank you Nescafe.
Results.Title: Keeps me smiling.

Results.ReviewText: I bought this for my husband as he only drink decaff, after he had drunk a few of cups of this product, he recommended me to try this product. It is the best coffee i ever had, i cannot tell the difference between this product and my normal coffee, its just full of flavour. Highly recommend it to all decaff drinker.
Results.Title: Full of flavour

Results.ReviewText: I saw this new product on the supermarket shelves this month and bought a jar as a couple of friends much prefer decaff.  I'm also a convert for the evening cuppa and was keen to try the Nescafe Gold Blendoption.  I'm impressed, love the taste, the after effects and the smoothness.  Top marks from me and my crew!
Results.Title: Just the ticket!

Results.ReviewText: I have bought this coffee for many years, to reduce my overall caffeine addiction. The rich, rounded flavour tricks my tastebuds into believing the caffeine is kicking in. It's the first thing I taste in the morning and the last thing at night. I wouldn't replace Nescafe Gold Blend Decaff with any other coffee.
Results.Title: Can't start the day without it!

Results.ReviewText: The quality of the coffee is good, but, I was not so keen on the taste.  I have had better coffee's.  I think it is difficult with decaff to get it right.  I have tried every single decaff out there and this is just average.  Nothing special and would not make me want to buy it again, unless I was desperate.
Results.Title: It was just ok

Results.ReviewText: I bought this on recommendation from a friend.  I have recently switched to almond milk and need a stronger coffee for this.  Nescafe gold blend decaff is perfect for this.  I love warming the almond milk then adding the coffee - feels really indulgent but healthier. Definitely one of the best on the market.
Results.Title: Great smooth taste

Results.ReviewText: Being a shift worker trying to find a decaf coffee that has a great taste to it rather than most decaf coffee’s just having a lovely aroma & basically no taste to it - this coffee has both lovely aroma to get your taste buds aroused & the smooth taste of a good coffee - won’t leave you feeling disappointed.
Results.Title: Wow coffee with a great taste

Results.ReviewText: I love coffee! But I am only able to drink decaff now and wasn't looking forward to the change. I was more than pleasantly surprised when I tried this coffee! It has a lovely taste, you would not know it wasn't standard caffeinated coffee! I now buy this at home and work, and everyone at work also loves it!
Results.Title: Love this Coffee!

Results.ReviewText: A long-time fan of Alta Rica I was disappointed with the new packaging in that I now cannot hold the jar due to arthritic hands.  The old jar was so shaped as to afford comfortable grip, whereas the new on is slippery (I dropped my first one) and is too full  to extract the first spoonful without spillage.
Results.Title: Retrograde step
